  "<b>Part 1: What is Spring?</b>:<br><br>Spring is one of the four seasons in the year, following winter and preceding summer. It is a time when nature begins to awaken from the cold, dormant period of winter. The weather becomes warmer, and plants, animals, and the environment begin to change and thrive again. Spring is often associated with new life, growth, and renewal.<br><br><b>Key Features of Spring:</b><br>1. <b>Warmer Weather</b>: After the cold winter, temperatures rise, making it more comfortable outside.<br>2. <b>Daylight Increases</b>: Days become longer, and there is more sunlight.<br>3. <b>New Growth</b>: Plants start to grow, flowers bloom, and trees begin to sprout leaves again.",
  
