  "<b>Part 1: What is Summer?</b>:<br><br>Summer is one of the four seasons of the year, typically associated with warm or hot weather. It comes after spring and before autumn. During summer, the days are longer, and the nights are shorter. Many people look forward to summer because it is a time for fun outdoor activities, vacations, and enjoying nature.<br><br>In some regions, summer can last for a few months, and it is marked by a rise in temperature. It is a time when many fruits and vegetables ripen, and animals are very active.",
  
  "<b>Part 2: Characteristics of Summer</b>:<br><br>Summer has several key characteristics that make it unique:<br><br>1. <b>Hot Weather</b><br>Definition: Summer is the hottest season of the year. The sun is stronger, and temperatures rise, especially in the middle of the day. People often wear lighter clothes like shorts and t-shirts to stay cool.<br><br>2. <b>Longer Days</b><br>Definition: One of the most noticeable features of summer is that the days are longer. The sun rises early and sets late, giving people more daylight hours to enjoy activities outside.<br><br>3. <b>Outdoor Activities</b><br>Definition: Summer is a time for fun outdoor activities. People go swimming, play sports, have picnics, go hiking, and visit beaches. Children often enjoy playing in parks, running through sprinklers, or riding bikes.<br><br>4. <b>Vacation Time</b><br>Definition: Many families take vacations in summer, traveling to the beach, countryside, or other fun destinations. Schools are often on holiday, giving children a break from their studies.<br><br>5. <b>Seasonal Foods</b><br>Definition: Summer is a time for fresh, delicious fruits and vegetables like watermelon, strawberries, and tomatoes. People also enjoy ice cream, cold drinks, and barbecue meals.",

