  "<b>Part 1: What Is Fall?</b>:<br><br>Fall, also known as autumn, is one of the four seasons of the year. It comes after summer and before winter. During fall, many changes occur in nature, and the weather becomes cooler. Fall is a special time when plants, animals, and the environment begin to prepare for winter.<br><br>To help students understand, show pictures or illustrations of fall scenes such as colorful trees, pumpkins, and harvest festivals. Ask them what they notice about the pictures:<br><br>Do the trees have many leaves or are they bare?<br>What colors can they see?<br>Are there any animals or pumpkins in the pictures?<br><br>These images will help students connect the idea of fall to the changes they observe in nature.",
  
