  "<b>Part 4: Class Activity and Review</b>:<br><br>To review the key concepts of seasonal changes, you can engage students with the following activities:<br><br><b>Picture Identification:</b><br>Show students pictures or illustrations of different seasons and ask them to identify the season based on the characteristics displayed (e.g., leaves falling, snow on the ground).<br><br><b>Discussion:</b><br>Ask the class how each season affects the plants and animals they see around them. Encourage them to think about what they observe in nature during each season and how it changes.<br><br><b>Seasonal Effects Worksheet:</b><br>Provide a worksheet where students match animals and plants with the season they are most associated with (e.g., bears in winter hibernating, flowers blooming in spring).",
  
